3:28 PM District Attorney in Court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Wesley John Eitel appeared via Zoom videoconferencing from Pierce County Jail.  Attorney Derek W Sanders appeared via Zoom videoconferencing from Pierce County Jail.  Court advises Defendant of charges and possible penalties.  Further reading waived.  Court advises Defendant of constitutional rights.  State requests $500 cash bond with conditions of absolute sobriety and no entry into bars, taverns or liquor stores.  DA Hatch states basis for cash bond request.  Atty. Sanders argues for signature bond, noting last offense was over ten years ago.  States Defendant does not qualify for PD but has limited income.  DA Hatch reiterates request for cash bond, noting public safety concerns.  Defendant responds.  Court orders $10,000 signature bond with conditions as requested. Court questions Defendant's address, phone, dob.  Disabled veteran.  Court advises Defendant of right to speedy Preliminary Hearing.  Defendant does not qualify for PD.  Would like county appointed paperwork.  Adjourned at 3:42 PM
